from imblearn.under_sampling import RandomUnderSampler
X_sample, y_sample = RandomUnderSampler(random_state=0).fit_resample(X, y)

from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
pipe = Pipeline([
    #('scaler', StandardScaler()),
    ('clf', LogisticRegression(random_state=0)),
])
params = {
    'clf__C': [0.0001, 0.001, 0.01, 0.1, 1.0, 10, 100],
}
grid_l = GridSearchCV(pipe, params, scoring='accuracy', cv=3)
grid_l_result = grid_l.fit(X, y)
print(grid_l.best_params_)
print(grid_l.best_score_)

from sklearn.model_selection import RandomizedSearchCV
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier

    #('scaler', StandardScaler()),
    ('clf', RandomForestClassifier(random_state=10)),
])

    'clf__max_depth': list(range(1,21)),
    'clf__n_estimators': list(range(10,110,10)),
    'clf__criterion': ["gini", "entropy"],
}
grid_r = GridSearchCV(pipe, params, scoring='accuracy', cv=5)

# KNN
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
pipe = Pipeline([
    #('scaler', StandardScaler()),
    ('clf', KNeighborsClassifier()),
])
params = {
    'clf__n_neighbors': list(range(5,10)),
}
grid_k = GridSearchCV(pipe, params, scoring='accuracy', cv=5)
grid_k_result = grid_k.fit(X, y)
print(grid_k.best_params_)
print(grid_k.best_score_)

Keras¶
In [64]:
from scikeras.wrappers import KerasClassifier
from keras import models
from keras import layers
def create_network(optimizer="rmsprop"):
    network = models.Sequential()
    network.add(layers.Dense(units=16, activation="relu", input_shape=(X.shape[1],)))
    network.add(layers.Dense(units=16, activation="relu"))
    network.add(layers.Dense(units=1, activation="sigmoid"))
    network.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy',
                    optimizer=optimizer, 
                    metrics=["accuracy"]) #  
    return network
